content.text:
I'll help analyze and provide instructions for building both structures shown in the main target image.

Left Structure Analysis:
- 3 layers
- Yellow blocks on top and bottom (horizontal orientation)
- Middle section has green blocks on sides with red and blue blocks in center
- Total of 6 blocks

Right Structure Analysis:
- 4 layers including roof
- Orange triangular roof pieces
- Blue vertical pieces
- Green and orange blocks in lower sections
- Total of 9 blocks

Let me provide the assembly instructions for each structure:

Left Structure:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 9 (bottom yellow horizontal block)
    Step2: Move block with index 8 (green vertical block)
    Step3: Move block with index 4 (red square block)
    Step4: Move block with index 1 (blue square block)
    Step5: Move block with index 8 (green vertical block)
    Step6: Move block with index 9 (top yellow horizontal block)
}

Right Structure:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 2 (green square block)
    Step2: Move block with index 3 (orange square block)
    Step3: Move block with index 2 (green square block)
    Step4: Move block with index 3 (orange square block)
    Step5: Move block with index 1 (blue square block)
    Step6: Move block with index 1 (blue square block)
    Step7: Move block with index 15 (orange triangular piece)
    Step8: Move block with index 15 (orange triangular piece)
    Step9: Move block with index 16 (orange triangular roof piece)
}

Each structure has been built from bottom to top, ensuring stability during construction. The blocks are used exactly as they appear in the dictionary without any rotation.
